            . I am a shopman to Mr. Dobree, a pawnbroker, in Charlotte-street, Fitzroy-square. On the 8th of August the prisoner pawned a flute in the name of Rose, London-street. In October he offered to pledge three, I questioned him, and his answers not being satisfactory. I took him to Mrs. Golding, and gave him in charge.</p>
